run as <script> <tree in preorder form with '.' for empty nodes, entered as space-separated values>

ref: https://stackoverflow.com/a/2676849/11064961

e.g. 1 2 4 . . 5 6 . . 7 . . 3 . . represents the tree

        1
       / \
      2   3
     / \
    4   5
       / \
      6   7

